<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-306-438  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 306 438.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  April 2 1990 v24 n14 p63(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Ford parts division has a better idea. (re-engineering effort cutsdelivery times, inventory and costs) (Ford Motor Co.)(includesrelated articles on Ford's mission and the benefits derived fromthe new automated parts distribution system)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Maglitta, Joseph.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Ford Motor Co's automated parts distribution system utilizesdecentralized IBM 4381 mainframes and an innovative 'carousel'warehousing system that is able to handle two to three milliontransactions per day.andP;  The re-engineering effort is geared towardsspeeding up the delivery of parts and improving order accuracy.andO;Scheduled for completion by mid-1991, the system has alreadyresulted in the elimination of 1.5 million square feet of partsinventory, faster delivery of priority orders from 72 to 48 hours,the closing of 10 regional parts distribution centers and increaseby about 45 percent shipments in certain large warehouses.andP;  Fordexecutives are also afforded better control of daily operationsbecause the system allows them to view the warehouses' operationsany time.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Ford Motor Co. (automation).andO;Ticker:    F.andO;Topic:     Automobile IndustryParts SupplyPerformance ImprovementInformation Systems.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>